I was going through the Apache source code looking for another bug, and some
code jumped out at me as being obviously wrong. Here's the (really short) patch:

--- proxy_util.c.orig   2006-11-01 20:05:21.000000000 +0100
+++ proxy_util.c        2006-11-01 20:05:56.000000000 +0100
@@ -955,7 +955,7 @@
                 *eos = 1;
             }
             else {
-                if (APR_SUCCESS != apr_bucket_read(e, (const char **)&response,
&len, APR_BLOCK_READ)) {
+                if (APR_SUCCESS != (rv = apr_bucket_read(e, (const char
**)&response, &len, APR_BLOCK_READ))) {
                     return rv;
                 }
                 /*


The same code is used a few lines earlier with the assignment i added in the
above patch, which convinces me that it really was an unintentional omission.
